text.section:
A local department may place a child in emergency shelter care before a hearing if:
Placement is required to protect the child from serious immediate danger;
There is no parent, guardian, custodian, relative, or other person able to provide supervision; and

section.section:
The Secretary of Human Resources, the Secretary of Juvenile Services, the Secretary of Health and Mental Hygiene, the State Superintendent of Schools, and the Special Secretary for Children, Youth, and Families, when appropriate, shall jointly adopt regulations to ensure that any child placed in shelter care in accordance with a petition filed under this section is provided appropriate services, including:
Health care services;
Mental health care services;
Counseling services;
Education services;
Social work services;
Drug and alcohol abuse assessment or treatment services; and
Visitation with siblings and biological family.
